<div class="text-justify">60th, 70th, 80th, 90th and 100th Birthdays are known as Shasthiabdhapoorthi, Beemaratha Shanthi, Sadhaabhishegam. These are conducted like a marriage with the required formalities at the premises of the Thirukadaiyur temple. It is believed that celebrating birthdays and marriages at Thirukadaiyur temple, Lord Shiva, Goddesses Parvathi and Lord Ganesh bless &amp; grant the couple, their children, besides their families and those participating in the celebration.... Long life, great happiness, peace, prosperity, good health, children marriages, good education, business &amp; professional promotions and so on.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">SHASHTI-ABDHA-POORTHI is celebrated on completion of 60 years of age. According to Indian Traditional Culture, every man as the Head of the Family is bound to delegate family duties like managing family properties to their children before attaining the age of 60 and concentrate more on Pious-activities... including Pilgrimage and pray for the welfare of the whole family……</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">BHEEMA-RATHA-SAANTHI is celebrated on completion of 70 years of age …. by the Children and Grandchildren… an opportunity to pay their gratitude to the Head of the Family.... This is the day the Grand-parents concentrate praying for the fulfillment of Family-ambitions, of Children and Grand-children. The 70 year's mrityu is conducted as a remedy to overcome the death fear, loss of money, loss of relatives etc.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">SATHA-ABHISHEKAM is celebrated on completion of 80 years of age. In fact, even strangers can walk in, when they hear a Sathabhishekam is celebrated to fall at the feet of the elders and seek their blessings. The person who has witnessed 1000 full moons CELEBRATES 80th BIRTHDAY. The Man completes all his Family-duties and Mundane-commitments... gets totally relieved from the Monetary-involvement, and surrender the duties to the children to run on their own independently on celebrating the 80th birthday….. Having completed his duties, he can now concentrate on prayers for the well-being of everyone…..and is free to leave the world towards Liberation from Rebirths... so as to obtain and be blessed with Mukthi Moksha.</div>
<div>All celebrations are performed in the year on completion of 60th, 70th, 80th and 100th.</div>
<div class="text-justify">Also and at the age of 59 one has to conduct Ukrathashanti, at the age of 69 shastiapatha poorthi, at 70 bheemaratha shanti, at 75 sahasra nakshatra shanti, at 80 sathaabhishekam, at 80 years 8 months sahasra chandra darisana shanti and at 100 years of age Kanakabishekam.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>Bheemaratha Shanthi 70</div>
<div>Satha abhishekham 80</div>
<div>Kanakabishekam 100</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">The best place to celebrate this tradition is THIRUKADAIYUR AMIRTHAKASESWARAR ABHIRAMI TEMPLE and is famous for celebrating these birthday marriages. It is believed that by conducting poojas, prayers and rituals here on the BIRTHDAY is highly meritorious. This is the only place in the world where these birthday marriages are held every day in large numbers according to one’s Indian zodiac. Markandeya, son of sage Mrikandu was predicted to live for only 16 years. As advised by his father, Markandeya worshiped Amritaghateswarar in Thirukkadaiyur, bringing the water from the Ganges, through an underground passage to the temple. On the destined day, Yama appeared with his noose. Markandeya sought refuge with the Lord and embraced the Shiva Lingam. The Lord warned Yama not to disturb Markandeya since he was under his protection. Yama did not listen and threw the noose that bound Markandeya and the Lingam together. Angered by this rash action, the Lord kicked Yama with his left leg and held him under his left foot, making him immobile. Markandeya was blessed with an ‘ever sixteen’ boon. It is believed that Lord Shiva diminished Kalan or Yaman in Thirukadaiyur. So Lord Shiva in Thirukadaiyur is called Mritunga Jaya Murthi.</div>
<div class="text-justify">It is the only place in the world, (good or bad days) where 50-100 numbers of aged birth day marriages are celebrated on a daily basis with all rituals and formalities.</div>
