<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">We are able to see several celebrities, actors, actress in cine field and others in better position, who has the kala sharpa effect i.e. Raghu Kethu yogam. So we can say Raghu kethu - Kala sharpa yogam will uplift you in future. Similarly Kala sharpa Dosha ie., Raghu Kethu Dosha will be unfavorable. In your previous birth if you have done some evil to the SHARPA KINGDOM - Kingdom of Snakes and for those who disturbed the life of Snakes in previous birth will get an effect of Kala Sharpa Dosham, such as Late Marriage, No improvement in Life, Failure is several life, Permanent Jobless situation, Divorce if married early, stress and depression may increase, gives the feeling of uncertainty. A Prayer and homam for Raghu Kethu at Thirupampuram temple can be conducted to achieve all the benefits of Raghu Kethu yogam and relief from Raghu Kethu Dosa. Whether you are rich or poor set aside some money to conduct the Yaham to benefit from Kala Sharpa Yoga and Dosha. Several people performed to gain benefit. One can achieve all the benefits by participating with pooja, prayer, Yaham conducted in Thirupampuram Temple and relieved from Raghu Kethu Dosa.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">Thirupampuram Paampuranathar Temple is another significant Lord Shiva temple. The village in and around the temple have no history of snake bites and anyone, who visits the temple, is protected from snake bites. The king of serpents “Nagaraja” is said to have worshipped Lord Shiva here. The name Paampuranathar is associated with Nagaraja. It is said that often a snake is seen surrounding the God or Goddess. Frangrance of Jasmine and Thazhampu is prominent in and around the temple. The legend says people never die of snake bites here, though there are many snakes seen and spotted around in this place. This is because once Lord Vinayagar was offering prayers to Lord Shiva and at that time the serpent, which was around the neck of Lord Shiva, thought that he too was being worshipped by Lord Vinayagar. “Lord Shiva” was much annoyed, when he came to know of this proudness of the snake around his neck and threw a curse on the snake serpents snatching the power on shakthi of poison.</div>
<div class="text-justify">Aadhiseshan and other serpents came to earth on this occasion of Mahashivrateri and offered prayers to Kudanthai Nageshwarar in the Morning, Thirunageshwaram at Noon, Thirupamburam Pambureswarar in the Evening and Nagoor Nageswarar in the Night and got the blessings of the Lord. On 26-05-2002 a snake had dropped its skin on the Lord Shiva Lingam like a garland at this temple. This is still preserved at the temple and can be seen at the Lord’s sannidhi. Besides no history of snake bites in this place, the banyan tree which is the in front of the temple does not let its Aerial prop roots to fall on the ground. ‘Agathi Keerai(Greens)’ does not blossom flowers neither in and around the temple nor in the whole Village. In fact the legend runs that the serpents with King Nagaraja Aadhiseshan conducted Yaham to please Lord Shiva and for which they used Agathi Keerai(Greens) flowers, and Banyan tree aerial prop roots to garland Lord Shiva. Lord Shiva appeared and gave back poisonous powers to serpents with a condition that they should bless benefit that those visit the temple and should not bite any one in and around the village. Further serpents had asked back Lord Shiva a boon that the Banyan trees of the temple should not let its aerial prop roots to ground and Agathi Keerai(Greens) should not blossom flowers so that others who come to pray to the great Lord Shiva should not use the Aerial prop roots and Agathi Keerai flowers and this act of prayer should remain unique only to the serpents. This is a scientific miracle, the serpent request and Lord blessings become true. Till to date the Agathi Keerai (Greens) is not blossom flowers in the village around the temple and Banyan tree infront of the temple does not let its aerial roots to reach the ground.</div>
