<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">Conducted as Yaaham for reliving from Saturn Sanieswara Bhagawan at Thirunarayur temple. Lord Sani Vishesha pooja and thailabhisekham is a good remedy for the traditional unfavorable influence of sanibhagawan. This pooja is best for those who suffer from Lord Saniswaran bad effects and unfavorable influence of Lord Sani based on astrology of 7 ½ years sanidosham, Ellarainattu Sani and also known as Astamasani, Panchama sani, Arthastama sani, sani Maha dosa, and Neecha sani'.</div>
<div class="text-justify">"Lord Sani" influences everyone since birth at certain juncture of life mostly with its evil effects. Not only human being, but also the Gods and Goddesses are being influenced by 'Lord Sani'. It is well known that the effect of Lord Sani brings extreme misery and losses. But if one propitiates Lord Sani and attains the virtuous effects of "Lord Sani's" blessings, gets devoid of the miseries and contracts prosperity in abundance, as experienced. At Thirunarayur the well-known holy temple which have divine effect of the pleasant 'Lord Sani' at pinnacle, also the seeking devotees prevails blessings to overcome all obstacles to attain salvation. Every human being in the universe enjoys both joys and sorrows according to the karmic effects in the past life. Lord Sani plays an important and special role amongst all the planets. Unlike the common perception, Lord Sani does not cause hurdles to anyone unnecessarily. It all depends upon the punya and papa effect that the person done in the previous jenmas birth. If person is consistently suffering from undue problems, it may be construed that he is under the influence of Lord Sani. However we can reduce the negative effects of Lord Sani by pleasing him in different ways and means so that one can lead a good and comfortable life.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">The SANI DOSHA NIVARANA POOJA YAAHAM being performed at Thirunarayur temple is considered to be the most auspicious for eradication of the evil effects of Lord Sani. Undoubtedly, the devotees who have congregated for this holy event, or those who happen to hear the chanting of holy spell 'OM SANICHARAYA NAMHA' thereof happen to be or great virtue accumulated in their life. You can achieve all the benefits by visiting and performing SANISWARA YAHAM at THIRUNARAIYUR TEMPLE. In Thirunaraiyur temple, Lord Saniswaran living with two wives and two children. He is also called as mangala saniswaran and this is the only temple in the world, where Lord Saniswaran available with his family members. It is considered to be an important place of Saturn worship. It is said that in no other place, including the famous Thirunallar temple, he is worshipped along with his two wives, Mandhadevi and Jyeshtadevi and his two sons, Maandhi and Kuligan.</div>
<div class="text-justify">In the ancient texts, black oil and black grams have given prominence to please Sani Bhagavan. According to Puranas, the body of Lord Vishnu creates three types of grams ie., black, white and wheat colored grams. These three are said to be very holy ones. These grams are used in homas. It is difficult to please the Sani Bhagavan. The duty of Lord Sani is to punish the persons for the sins they have committed in previous jenma. To please Sani Bhagavan, one has to surrender themselves to Sani Bhagavan and offer prayers to please him. Offer prayers to Lord Shiva, Feeding poor people with food duly mixed with salt, Donating black dress to poor people on Saturday, Perform tailabhishekam to Lord Sani, Perform abishekam to Lord Shiva, Feed the black dogs, crows, black cow, Perform sindur puja to Lord Hanuman on Saturday.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">According to the legend when King Dasaratha ruled the entire world, Saturn was to pass through Rohini star after staying in Krithigai, on one occasion. Sage Vasishta and others told Dasaratha that if Saturn did so, it would spell doom for the world. There would be famine everywhere for 12 years and animals, human beings would be put to much hardship. He requested Dasaratha to prevent it. Dasaratha immediately got into his fast-moving chariot, carrying all Divine weapons and reached the star, Rohini. He saw Saturn moving in his golden chariot towards Rohini and sent the Divine weapons including the “Samhara Asthram” towards him. Saturn, laughing at the king’s futile attempts, told him that He could destroy anybody by His mere look. The powers that Dasaratha had got through severe penance, austerity and Divine grace prevented Saturn from eliminating him. Dasaratha requested Saturn not to pass through Rohini and thus spare the world from experiencing famine for 12 years. Saturn was immensely pleased with the king’s concern for the welfare of his subjects and granted two requests. He also told him that if he visited Thirunaraiyur and bathed in the tank there he would appear before him. Dasaratha agreed and Saturn appeared before him. As Thirunaraiyur is the place where he appeared before Dasaratha, it is considered to be an important place of Saturn worship. It is said that in no other place, including the more famous Thirunallar temple, is he worshipped along with his two wives, Mandhadevi and Jyeshtadevi and his two sons, Maandhi and Kuligan. According to the sthalapuranam, Lord Rama and Anjaneya, during their return from Lanka to Ayodhya, visited this place. Though a sub-shrine of the Ramanathaswami temple in Thirunaraiyur, which is also called as Saneeswarar Thirukkoil, Saturn’s abode here has separate Dhwajasthambam, Balipeetam and the crow mount in front of it. The sthalavriksham is “erukku” and the holy water source is known as Rama Theertham. The temple is agog with activity on Saturdays and during the Gurupeyarchi and Sanipeyarchi. The presiding deity in the main temple is Ramanathaswami, facing east, and it is considered to be as holy as in Rameswaram. Many devotees, who are unable to visit Rameswaram, make their offerings to the Lord here.</div>
            </div>
        </div>
