<div class="text-justify">Thiruvenkadu temple blesses to have healthy progeny, possession of fertile lands and eliminate difficulties. THIRUVENKADU is a famous Navagraha temple dedicated to Lord Shiva and the planet Mercury, one of the nine Navagrahas. There is a separate Sannidhi for Bhudhan - Mercury. This temple is especially known for its unique incarnation of Lord Shiva called "Agora Murthi. Thiruvengadu village is also famous for its unique structure of pools in temples. This temple has 3 pools, 3 Gods. It is a belief that who bath in all these THREE pools, one will be BLESSED WITH MALE CHILD and free from their problems like diseases, delay in marriage, etc., Lord Shiva opened his 3rd eye and killed the demon. The Agoramurthy form of Lord Shiva can be seen in the idol, which is the expression of his anger. It is also said that one who worships this form - Agoramurthy of Lord Shiva can never have enemies. This is the place where Lord Shiva performed the six different tandavas or dance forms. This is also well-known as Adhi Chidambaram.</div>
<div class="text-justify">THIRUVENKADU is a famous Navagraha temple dedicated to Lord Shiva and the planet Mercury, one of the nine Navagrahas. There is a separate Sannidhi for Bhudhan - Mercury. The temple is huge and all four important Saivite saints have sung in praise of this Lord. There is a reference to this temple in the Valmiki Ramayana. The oldest part of the temple is more than 3000 years old. Bhudhan is said to bestow wisdom and intellect. Budha Pooja or Mercury Pooja is dedicated to planet Mercury. Budha Pooja on Wednesdays brings in manifold benefits like eliminating difficulties, healthy progeny, possession of fertile lands, etc. Among the Nine Planets Navagraha, Budhan is said to bestow wisdom and intellect. . Offering pooja to Bhuda Bhagavan on Wednesdays is believed to rectify Bhuda Dhosham. Those who visit Thiruvengadu will find relief from puthira dosham, difficulties in studies, mental instability, and nervous disorders. Knowledge, music, astrology, math, sculpting, medicine, and language skills are the beneficial aspects of Bhudan. Offering Bhudan with full green moong dhal, white flowers and green cloth is believed to bring Sastra Gnanam to devotees.</div>
