<div  class="text-justify">PRATYANGIRA DEVI Temple Kumbakonam - The Pratyangira aspect of the Divine has been a bit of a secret for most of bygone ages. Many believed that direct experience with this energy was reserved for Saints and Rishis. Seeing Pratyangira in any form was considered an enormous blessing. Prayer and Pooja are performed mainly to protect oneself from black magic and to prosper in life. Advantages of this prayer and sadhana are many including tremendous Vak siddhi, Karya siddhi, healthy body, full protection from accidents and sudden deaths and people, who are dumb are also benefitted. She punishes the enemies of her devotees. The temple was built amidst eight cemeteries, burning ghats and no archanai or abishekam is performed in this temple. Only homam is done on “no moon nights” and the main ingredient for the homam is dried chillies thrown in tonnes, in the homan fire, but it is surprising to note, that the chillies do not harm anyone participating in the homan, while it is burning in the fire. Normally the red chillies smoke while burnt in fire harm humanss and cause nonstop cough. But this does not happen while tons of chillies are thrown into Homam fire at this temple. Performing yagams, homams and prayers to the Goddess, protects true devotees from enemies and even punishes enemies and wins over their evil plotting. If you are a true devotee she is the most wonderful mother.</div>
