<div class="text-justify">Golden chariot &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; possible to pull golden chariot around temple inner passage path (prakharam) on any day desired.</div>
<div class="text-justify">KOLLAMKUDI KALI AMMAN TEMPLE - Criminals, Thieves, Cheaters, Liars, Rowdies, who cheat the poor and innocent, those who are unjust, those who do not repay the borrowed money are punished by Kollamkudi Kali and those affected are instantly benefitted. Punish the wicked and Protector of the Innocent. Sage Agasthiar once did penance to change barren land to fertile lands around this region for the benefit of the people. Goddess Kali appeared and changed the land into a prosperous area by bringing regular rains. By worshiping Kali Amman people are blessed.</div>
<div class="text-justify">An actual incident that happened 75 years ago involved three thieves who planned to steal the jewels of Kaliamman. After stealing the jewels they decided to scale the wall and escape. The first thief fell down from top of the wall and broke his leg. The other two managed to climb down safely. The injured however, advised the other two to return the jewels and surrender to Goddess Kali. Not heeding his warning, the other two thieves rode away on their cycles. While crossing the village border they were hit by a lorry and died on the spot. The bag containing the jewels was found hanging from the handlebar of the cycle. This incident can be found in the police records. Kaliamman is considered to deliver justice and worshiped by devotees from all over the world.</div>
             </div>
