<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">PRANANATHESWARAR temple, Thirumangalakudi .... Once King Kulothunga's minister Alaivanar was building a temple from the tax collected without obtaining the King's permission. The King beheaded him when he came to know about this. As his last wish, the minister requested that he be cremated in Thirumangalakudi. His wife prayed to the Mangalambikai at Thirumangalakudi and brought back her husband to life. So women pray to the Goddess here, for the long life and well-being of their husbands. The circumambulating procedure is very different from other temples. One must go in an anticlockwise direction and worship Saneeswaran, Budhan, Angarakan, Chandran, Kethu, Shukran and Rahu before worshiping Chandikeswarar and then proceed in a clockwise direction and return to worship Kol Theertha Vinayakar. Finally, prostrate or do a namaskaram near the Dhwajasthambam. Nine pradarshanams of the outer praharam is recommended. The temple priests do uchi kala pooja at 12 o’noon on Sundays and offer hot curd rice nivethiyam to lord. After the prayer the hot curd rice is given to devotees in a “vella errukku leaf” - holy plant. It is belived that those eat the prasatham of hot curd rice from the “vella errukku leaf” for 11 continued Sundays will get cured all type of skin diseases.</div>
