            <div class="card-body">
              <div class="text-justify">Pooja, Astrology, Homam and Prayer can be conducted @ La Woods Hotel Chennai or La Woods Hotel Site Thiruvannamalai</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">POOJA is a sacred practice that Hindu people perform on different occasions to show respect to their deities. It is considered as an act of showing reverence to the Almighty through invocations, prayers, slokas, bhajans, and rituals. According to Hinduism, Pooja brings a spiritual connection between the deity and the devotee.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">BUDHA POOJA or Mercury Pooja is dedicated to the planet Mercury. Budha Pooja on Wednesdays bring in manifold benefits like eliminating difficulties, healthy progeny and possession of fertile lands. Bhudhan is ruled by Lord Maha Vishnu.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">CHANDRA POOJA is dedicated to Lord Chandra, the Moon God, who rules our mind and the pooja brings success. Grah Shanti Chandra Pooja is recommended to those, having malefic Chandra or wrongly placed moon in the horoscope.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">GURU POOJA is dedicated to the planet Jupiter. Grah Shanti Guru Pooja is recommended to those, having malefic Planet Guru or wrongly placed Planet Jupiter in the horoscope. And pooja blesses education and knowledge. Also cures ailments and cleanses negative emotions.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">HANUMAN POOJA is beneficial for those who want to gain strength, wisdom and knowledge. The worship of Shri Hanumanji, is believed to endow courage to fight any illness. Hanuman Pooja provides peace of mind.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">KALI POOJA is a fervent prayer to the fearsome, ferocious Goddess. The aim of Kali Pooja is to seek the help of Maa Kali in destroying evil. This Kali Pooja is performed to diminish ego and the negative tendencies that hamper spiritual growth.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">KETU POOJA Pooja is dedicated to the planet Ketu. Grah Shanti Ketu Pooja or Worship is recommended for those, having malefic Ketu or wrongly placed Planet Ketu in the horoscope.This Pooja makes the life stronger, instrumental in strengthening power, converting even enemies as friends.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">MARS POOJA Mangal Pooja or Mars Worship is dedicated to the planet Mars. Grah Shanti Mangal Pooja liberates from debts, poverty and skin problems. It is recommended for those having the Mangal in the wrong place in the horoscope.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">RAHU POOJA or the Dragon's Head Worship is dedicated to planet Rahu. Grah Shanti Rahu Pooja is recommended for those, having or wrongly placed Planet Rahu in the horoscope. This Pooja brings prosperity and negates bad effects, illness etc. Besides gaining good health and wealth.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">SATYANARAYANA POOJA can be performed on any day. However, Purnima, Full Moon Night and Sankranti are considered as the most auspicious days. The appropriate time of Pooja is in the evening but a prayer conducted in the morning is equal beneficial.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">SHANI POOJA is done to appease planet Saturn. Grah Shanti Shani Pooja is sought for mental peace and to get rid of various diseases. It is recommended for those, having malefic Planet Shani or wrongly placed Planet Saturn in the horoscope. Shani ensures happiness and known to affect adversely on occasions when he occupies certain positions in the horoscope. Conducting Shani pooja will overcome all these issues and mitigate hardships. Planet Shani is ruled by Lord Yama.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">SHUKRA - VENUS POOJA is conducted to appease planet Venus. Grah Shanti Shukra Pooja is recommended for those, having or wrongly placed Planet Venus in the horoscope. The pooja showers knowledge of art and music. And bestow long life, wealth, happiness, children, property and good education. He is ruled by Goddess Lakshmi.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">SURYA POOJA or Sun Worship is dedicated to Lord Surya. Grah Shanti Surya Pooja is recommended to those, having malefic surya or wrongly placed Planet Sun in the horoscope. Sun is the most powerful God and this pooja bestows good health and prosperity.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">TULSI POOJA Tulsi is a sacred plant which can be found in almost every Hindu home. Tulsi Pooja or worship of the Tulsi plant is performed, almost every day.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">ASTROLOGY SERVICES Vedic Astrology is the science of studying the planetary positions as per the date, time and place of birth of a person. It has been a part of human culture from ancient times and is deeply rooted in almost all civilizations. Vedic Astrology has flourished for several thousand years and is renowned for its spiritual depth and accuracy in predicting future events. Based on the surreal zodiac, it reflects an astrologer's perception of the placement of the planets in the constellations. A birth chart, also known as Kundli, Janma Kundali, Janampatri, Vedic horoscope, Jathaka is prepared, which captures the precise astronomical positions of stars and planets at the individual's time of birth. This information is used to predict future events.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">INDIAN VASTU SHASTRA also known as Vastu Veda is the “science of construction”. It is a traditional Hindu system of design based on directional alignments. In Indian architecture, the home is regarded as a shrine. According to Vastu Shastra, the world comprises of five basic elements known as the pancha maha bhoota. The five elements are as follows - EARTH, WATER, AIR, FIRE, and SPACE. There is an invisible and constant relation among all the five elements. It is believed that a person can improve his status by designing his buildings in conjunction with the effectiveness of these five natural forces. Vastu Shastra combines all the five elements of nature and balances them with the individual and the material. Taking advantage of the benefits bestowed by the five elements of nature to create a congenial living and working environment thereby facilitating spiritual well-being and paving the way for enhanced health, prosperity and happiness.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">MAHAGANAPATHI HOMAM Performing Ganapathy Homam at least once in a year will bestow prosperity, health, wealth and peace of mind to the individual. Ganapathy Homam should be performed on all auspicious occasions before starting a new project or grihapravesham or getting married or to remove obstacles.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">PITHRU SHANTHI HOMAM Pithru Karyiam or Oblations are conducted for the peace of the departed souls. Homam is done in the name of Athma, name and star of the deceased person to give mukthi or salvation to the souls of deceased parents, relatives and ancestors. The performer of the homam gets relieved of all adverse effects due to the restlessness of the souls and the curse of forefathers.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">NAVAGRAHA HOMAM This homam has the power to counter flaws in the horoscope and enables a person to prosper in life in case astrological defects are the main blocks to his well-being and appease the nine planets i.e. the Sun, Moon, Mars, Mercury, Jupiter, Venus, Saturn, Rahu and Ketu. Sun for health, Moon for success, Mars for wealth, Mercury for knowledge, Jupiter for education, Venus for art and music, Saturn for happiness and confidence, Rahu for strength and Ketu for prosperity.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">CHANDI HOMAM Chandi Homam is performed to remove any obstacles or hurdles in growth – both internally and externally and the sufferings resulting from poison, sorcery, thieves etc. By performing Chandi homam, one can attain health, wealth, prosperity, fame, success, strength, prevent ailments, danger and avoid defeat in the hand of adversaries.</div>
<div class="text-justify">AYUSH HOMAM This Homam is performed to Lord Shiva to ensure longevity in life. The best remedy is to perform Ayush Homam on every birthday, as reckoned by the tamil birth-star and not by the English birth date, which can help avoid untimely and unfortunate death.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">PROGENY SANTHANA GOPALA, PUTRA KAMESHTI HOMAM This Homam is a boon to perform if there are obstacles or delay in getting progeny or some complications during pregnancy. It can also be performed by a childless couple, to beget a child. Expectant mothers can also perform this pooja for healthy and intelligent children.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">PRATHYANGIRA HOMAM Prathyangira Homam is performed for destruction of negative forces like disease, obstacles, rivalry or to regain power, removal of evil effects of enemies, Shathru Dosha and Shathru Bhaya Nivarana. This Homam is performed to prevent major accidents and any health issues caused due to poisoning.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">HOMAMS TO GET MARRIED Homams can also be performed for people who want to get married and remove any obstacles that are delayed marriage. The bride or groom will be blessed with a suitable spouse and enjoy a good relationship. Those who have kuja dosha i.e bad position of Mars in their natal chart can perform this homam and nullify the effects of the planets.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">MAHA MRUTHUNJAYA HOMAM Maha Mruthyunjaya Homam is dedicated to Lord Shiva, to avoid premature death, or Victory over Mruthyu for longevity, cure for chronic illness and healthy life, lessen the dangers to life due to accidents and serious illness removing evil effects of enemies and Shathru Dosha Nivarana.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">ABHYANKARA HOMAM strengthens the mind and removes fear. The presiding deity Indra-Abhyankara is appeased with the offering of ghee, Havis, cooked rice and Special Sticks known as samith in the fire.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">SUDARSHANA HOMAM The Sudarshana Chakram is the mighty weapon of Lord Narayana and has many auspicious attributes associated with it. “Pida Pradanam” which gives immediate relief from pain and suffering, “Papa Nashanam”, the destruction of sins. Performing Sudarshana Homam confers health, wealth and prosperity and bestows spirituality.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">MAHALAKSHMI HOMAM Lakshmi is the Goddess of wealth and prosperity, and is the divine spouse of Lord Vishnu. The worship of Lakshmi brings about prosperity with a sense of responsibility.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">POUSHNA HOMAM Lord Poosha the presiding deity of this Homam helps a person recover from anaemia and other blood related problems. Lord Poosha is appeased by offering ghee, Havis cooked rice and Special Sticks known as samith in the fire.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">SANTHANA GOPALA HOMAM is performed with prayers to Lord Vishnu. The devotee performing this Homam is believed to gain healthy successors, success in all his ventures and attain fulfillment in worldly life.</div>
<div class="text-justify">LAKSHMI KUBERA HOMAM is performed for the purpose of gaining legitimate wealth and prosperity in life, to invoke riches dispelling any curse or obstacle, faster recovery of dues, solving financial problems and receive the blessings of Goddess Lakshmi.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">DHANVANTHRI HOMAM is very useful for curing serious diseases and if performed once in a year with the atmosphere of positive energy, the ill effects of health is reduced. Dhanvanthari is the physician of Gods, and the Father of Indian Medicine.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">SURYASOOKTA HOMAM is performed to recover from eye related disorders. The presiding deity Agni &amp; Vishnu are appeased by offering ghee, Havis, cooked rice and Special Sticks known as samith in the fire.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">TILA HOMAM Ancestors are invoked in this Homam and appeased by the offering of ghee, Havis cooked rice and Special Sticks known as samith in the fire. The Homam is performed to please the ancestors so that their blessings are always with us for success in all endeavors.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">VIRAJAA HOMAM Through this Homam, Lord Parmeshwara, the presiding deity gives his blessings to calm the agitated mind and the mind not only becomes cleansed of all negative energies but also acquires peace and tranquility.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">UDAGASHANTHI HOMAM This Homam if performed gives peace of mind in abundance to the performer. Presiding deity is Lord Varuna.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">VAISHVANARA HOMAM When the presiding deity of this homam, Agni- Vaishvanaraha is pleased, he cures kidney related problems as well as ASCITES.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">AIKAMATYA SOOKTA HOMAM AND APARTHIRATHA SOOKTA HOMAM This Homam is performed to invoke Lord Indra to bless with the strength to overcome obstacles.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">HANUMAN CHALISA GURU HOMAM This Homam is performed 100 times to solve legal problems and to get rid of all fears.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div class="text-justify">POUSNA SOOKTA HOMAM Chanting the mantra invokes the presiding deity Surya, to give remedy for anaemic disorders.</div>
<div class="text-justify">RUDRA HOMAM is a remedy for people suffering from stomach disorders. This Homam is chanted 121 times and the presiding deity is Sri Rudran.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>HIKKA NIVURUTHI HOMAM is performed to get relief from a various speech disabilities.</div>
<div>INDRAAMHOMUK HOMAM is performed for the removal of sins.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>LALITHA SAHASRANAMAM HOMAM Chanting of Lalita Sahasranamam for 108 times, gives health, wealth and happiness.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>PUTRAKAMA HOMAM is performed to invoke the blessings of Agni &amp; Indra for a healthy and intelligent male child.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>RINAHARAMANGALASTOTRA HOMAM invokes Lord Mangala to relieve the performer from debts and worries.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>SOORYA NAMASKARAM LAGHU This japam is performed 8 times to maintain good eye sight and a healthy heart.</div>
			 </div>
        </div>
    </div><!-- end single accrodian -->
